oakcurric:unit-2687
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Being curious about printing"@en ;
  curric:slug "being-curious-about-printing" ;
  rdfs:comment """Pupils will develop essential print making skills, explore connections between
  media and materials. They will learn to control various printmaking tools and be aware of
  the sustainability of their materials. They will recycle tetrapak and card to make their
  print blocks."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit supports pupils as they integrate the important concept of
  sustainability into their artistic practice. Building on their existing skills, pupils will
  learn to create prints that are environmentally conscious and promotes sustainable practices.
  This unit promotes critical thinking, innovation, and responsibility. It prepares pupils for
  future art projects by encouraging them to consider the environmental impact of their work
  and to think creatively about sustainable solutions.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2687-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2687-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2687-3 ;
  curric:id "2687"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.824086Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-art-and-design-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-digital ,
    oakcurric:thread-print ,
    oakcurric:thread-design .

oakcurric:unit-2680
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "The importance of nature in art"@en ;
  curric:slug "art-craft-and-design-from-around-the-world" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils will explore art, artefacts, and architecture from around the
  world. Through hands-on activities, they will experiment with different techniques and
  materials to create artworks. Pupils will gain a wider context of how art shapes and
  reflects our global history overtime."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit broadens pupils understanding of the relationship between
  artists in the west and globally. At this stage, students are developing critical thinking
  and creative skills, making it an ideal time to continue their exploration of a shared
  language developed between artists from different global perspectives This unit encourages
  pupils to appreciate different perspectives, fostering a broader worldview and inspiring
  their own artistic techniques.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2680-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2680-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2680-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2680-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2680-5 ;
  curric:id "2680"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.084431Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-art-and-design-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-paint ,
    oakcurric:thread-print ,
    oakcurric:thread-textiles ,
    oakcurric:thread-draw ,
    oakcurric:thread-design ,
    oakcurric:thread-sculpt .

oakcurric:unit-2676
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "An overview of art"@en ;
  curric:slug "an-overview-of-art" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils enhance their critical thinking exploring art from various
  perspectives. They discuss what defines art, study galleries and museums and art's
  connection to the curriculum. They consider drawing and how emotions are expressed using
  this medium."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit is useful for pupils as they transition to secondary school,
  where they will encounter more complex and diverse ideas. By exploring what defines art and
  examining its role across various contexts, pupils develop critical thinking and analytical
  skills. This unit encourages them to question and appreciate art's multifaceted nature,
  preparing them for more advanced art studies. Addressing common challenges like drawing
  confidence helps build resilience and fosters a growth mindset in their artistic journey.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2676-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2676-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2676-3 ;
  curric:id "2676"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.086862Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-art-and-design-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-draw ,
    oakcurric:thread-digital ,
    oakcurric:thread-paint ,
    oakcurric:thread-sculpt ,
    oakcurric:thread-collage .

oakcurric:unit-2736
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Personal identity"@en ;
  curric:slug "personal-identity" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit explores personal identity in art through self-expression, mapping,
  storytelling, and the interplay between personal and universal themes. Pupils will engage
  with a variety of art forms while considering how identity is shaped and communicated."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In this final unit before GCSEs it is vital that pupils begin to explore
  their own sense of self and their own creative desires through various provcations. This unit
  is situated here to begin to support more independent choice making, allowing for pupils to
  have more ownership over their learning and creative practice, which is needed at the next
  level.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2736-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2736-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2736-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2736-4 ;
  curric:id "2736"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.244878Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-art-and-design-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-paint ,
    oakcurric:thread-draw ,
    oakcurric:thread-design .

oakcurric:unit-3745
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Art for life: expression and belonging"@en ;
  curric:slug "art-for-wellbeing-expression-and-belonging" ;
  rdfs:comment """Pupils will explore how creative making can support health and wellbeing through
  personal expression and use art for self-discovery. Inspired by artistic practice they
  will investigate art as a tool for transformation and connection, using memories and
  reflections to support a sense of belonging."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit encourages pupils to delve into personal expression and
  self-discovery through art. Building on their existing skills, pupils will learn to
  articulate their thoughts, emotions, and experiences visually. This unit promotes expression,
  critical thinking, and creativity. It prepares pupils for more advanced art projects by
  encouraging them to explore and communicate personal narratives and connections through their
  work.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3745-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3745-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3745-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3745-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3745-5 ;
  curric:id "3745"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.253458Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-art-and-design-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-print ,
    oakcurric:thread-collage ,
    oakcurric:thread-paint .

oakcurric:unit-2685
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Abstract painting: sustainable materials"@en ;
  curric:slug "abstract-painting-sustainable-materials" ;
  rdfs:comment """Pupils will develop their understanding of abstract painting and make more
  sophisticated connections. They will build confidence in taking risks with new ideas, look
  at different tools and techniques, and learn to communicate with symbols and marks."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit encourages pupils to delve into personal expression and
  self-discovery through art. Building on their existing skills, pupils will learn to
  articulate their thoughts, emotions, and experiences visually. This unit promotes emotional
  intelligence, critical thinking, and creativity. It prepares pupils for more advanced art
  projects by encouraging them to explore and communicate personal narratives and connections
  through their work.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2685-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2685-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2685-3 ;
  curric:id "2685"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.567640Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-art-and-design-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-paint ,
    oakcurric:thread-draw .

oakcurric:unit-2735
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Social action"@en ;
  curric:slug "social-action" ;
  rdfs:comment """Pupils will explore social action in a variety of forms, from collaborative
  practice to inndividual action and how art works can challenge ideas and influenece
  decisions. These lessons encourage critical thinking and self-expression, fostering
  creativity, empathy, and social awareness."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit deepens pupils understanding of socially engaged art and how
  creative practitioners tackle important societal issues. Building on their existing skills,
  pupils will learn to create meaningful and thought-provoking artworks that reflect
  contemporary concerns. This unit promotes critical thinking, emotional awareness, and an
  understanding of the role of art in society. It prepares pupils for more advanced art
  projects by encouraging them to explore complex themes and develop a personal artistic voice.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2735-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2735-2 ;
  curric:id "2735"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.571435Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-art-and-design-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-print ,
    oakcurric:thread-collage ,
    oakcurric:thread-draw ,
    oakcurric:thread-sculpt ,
    oakcurric:thread-design .

oakcurric:unit-2681
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "The elements of art"@en ;
  curric:slug "the-elements-of-art" ;
  rdfs:comment """Pupils will develop an understanding of the basic elements of art and learn how
  artists use these elements in different ways in their work. In the unit, pupils will
  answer questions as they look at the elements through a variety of processes to identify
  how they are used in different art forms."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In previous units pupils have been introduced to the introductions of Art,
  Craft and Design. This unit moves into the technical, through the elements of art which form
  the building blocks of the subject. Looking at each of the elements in turn and how different
  artforms and artists have interpretted them in their work.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2681-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2681-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2681-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2681-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2681-5 ;
  curric:id "2681"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.599819Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-art-and-design-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-paint ,
    oakcurric:thread-collage ,
    oakcurric:thread-draw ,
    oakcurric:thread-sculpt .

oakcurric:unit-2733
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "The principles of art"@en ;
  curric:slug "the-principles-of-art" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit expands pupils understanding of the foundations of creative practice,
  building on knowledge of the elements of art, to now explore more complex principles. This
  will deepen understanding of how artists use these principles to question the world around
  them and communicate their ideas."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In previous units pupils have been introduced to the elements of art which
  form the building blocks of the subject. This unit builds on the elements with the principles
  of art, in which pupils understand how to critique work using the fundamental concepts. The
  pupils are able to articulate their thoughts and opinions about artwork using more complex
  subject specific vocabulary.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2733-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2733-2 ;
  curric:id "2733"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.606133Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-art-and-design-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-digital ,
