    oakcurric:thread-design ,
    oakcurric:thread-textiles .

oakcurric:unit-2683
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Being curious about spatial design and architecture"@en ;
  curric:slug "spatial-design-architecture-and-interiors-working-collaboratively-to-a-brief" ;
  rdfs:comment """Pupils will explore architecture and the built environment, learning about form,
  volume, domestic and public buildings, cultural structures, and materials. Lessons will
  enhance understanding of architectural principles, appreciation for styles, and skills in
  perspective drawing and design."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit introduces pupils to the fundamental concepts and principles of
  architecture. Building on their existing art skills, pupils will learn to appreciate the
  built environment and understand the role of architecture in shaping our world. This unit
  promotes critical thinking, creativity, and an appreciation for cultural and historical
  contexts. It prepares pupils for more advanced art and design studies by encouraging them to
  explore complex forms and structures through both theoretical and practical approaches.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2683-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2683-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2683-3 ;
  curric:id "2683"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.608013Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-art-and-design-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-digital ,
    oakcurric:thread-draw ,
    oakcurric:thread-design .

oakcurric:unit-2734
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Identity: exploring portraiture"@en ;
  curric:slug "identity-exploring-portraiture" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit explores portraiture’s power in expressing identity, culture, and
  belief. Pupils will study artists who challenge stereotypes and explore power,
  representation, and concealment. They will develop critical thinking while reinforcing
  respect, tolerance, and self-expression."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit builds on prior learning about identity and draws inspiration
  from the Equality Act 2010 and protected characteristics. Centered on British values, it
  fosters pupils’ understanding of their own identity and their right to self-identify,
  promoting tolerance and respect for diversity. The unit also enhances their art skills and
  critical thinking while introducing how artists explore identity and challenge stereotypes.
  It lays the groundwork for future discussions on identity, essential for their progression
  into GCSE, by scaffolding creative conversations around identity and diversity.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2734-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2734-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2734-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2734-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2734-5 ;
  curric:id "2734"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.610066Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-art-and-design-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-paint ,
    oakcurric:thread-draw ,
    oakcurric:thread-sculpt .

oakcurric:unit-2682
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Textiles and the creative industries"@en ;
  curric:slug "being-curious-about-textiles" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit starts by offering pupils insights into diverse career opportunities
  within the creative industries, looking at Fashion in more detail. It leads into a
  textiles unit exploring different elements of textiles and fabric manipulation"""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit builds on pupils' existing skills by enhancing their ability to
  research, analyse, and understand the creative industries. Learning about the economic impact
  and roles of creative institutions enhances their awareness of the broader context of their
  artistic practice. Investigating creative jobs, networks, and funding opportunities builds on
  their knowledge of career development and professional practice. Exploring career progression
  fosters their ability to plan and set goals for their future.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2682-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2682-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2682-3 ,
