oakcurric:unit-2679
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Art movements"@en ;
  curric:slug "art-movements-and-art-periods" ;
  rdfs:comment """Pupils will analyse and critique a selection of western art movements and
  understand their wider historical relevance. Pupils will engage with practical tasks to
  gain an understanding of the defining techniques and materials used as well as writing a
  manifesto."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit broadens pupils understanding of how the movements connect with
  a wider historical context. The unit looks at key western art movements in more depth and
  with chronological awareness. It sets a backdrop for engaging with artworks and artists with
  more depth of understanding and taking part in analysis and discussions.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2679-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2679-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2679-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2679-4 ;
  curric:id "2679"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.727090Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-art-and-design-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-digital ,
    oakcurric:thread-draw ,
    oakcurric:thread-paint .

oakcurric:unit-2678
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "An overview of design"@en ;
  curric:slug "an-overview-of-design" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit helps pupils to define design and understand the roles of designers and
  architects. They will study traditional and contemporary practices and research
  influential designers. Lessons will enhance understanding, foster creativity, and develop
  research and critical thinking skills."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit expands pupils' awareness of real-life creative industries as it
  introduces them to the vast field of design, which hones the applied aspect of their artistic
  development. It builds on their existing knowledge and encourages them to think creatively
  about how design impacts the world around them. Understanding the principles and history of
  design prepares pupils for more advanced art and design studies, fostering a deep
  appreciation for the role of design in everyday life.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2678-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2678-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2678-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2678-4 ;
  curric:id "2678"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.783019Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-art-and-design-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-textiles ,
    oakcurric:thread-draw ,
    oakcurric:thread-design ,
    oakcurric:thread-print ,
    oakcurric:thread-digital .

oakcurric:unit-3744
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Connections: home, space and family"@en ;
  curric:slug "connections-home-space-and-family" ;
  rdfs:comment """Pupils will explore the theme of family in art and how ideals of what a family is
  has changed over time. The unit builds on both the history of familial connections in art,
  as well as exploring contemporary forms of family. Pupils will explore the theme of family
  through 3d forms."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit encourages pupils to consider the notion of the family in all of
  its diversity. This will encourage a deeper reflection and analysis of the various nuances
  within this theme, at a time when pupils increasingly seek to articulate diverse experiences.
  This complexity of thought will be needed as they move into their exam years and will be
  supported creatively through more symbolic forms of communication, as well as being inspired
  by more sculptural forms of practice.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3744-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3744-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3744-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3744-4 ;
  curric:id "3744"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.878697Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-art-and-design-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-draw ,
    oakcurric:thread-paint ,
    oakcurric:thread-print ,
    oakcurric:thread-sculpt ,
    oakcurric:thread-design .

oakcurric:unit-2686
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Collage and Assemblage: sustainable materials"@en ;
  curric:slug "being-curious-about-collage-and-assemblage" ;
  rdfs:comment """Pupils will develop their collaging skills and showcase their strengths. They will
  learn about the different between using the metholody as part of the process or as the
  technique. They will explore how to place images together and develop compositional skills
  as well as be playful with ideas."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit supports pupils as they integrate the important concept of
  sustainability into their artistic practice. Building on their existing skills, pupils will
  learn to create collages that are environmentally conscious and promotes sustainable
  practices. This unit promotes critical thinking, innovation, and responsibility. It prepares
  pupils for future art projects by encouraging them to consider the environmental impact of
  their work and to think creatively about sustainable solutions.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2686-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2686-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2686-3 ;
  curric:id "2686"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.882603Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-art-and-design-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-draw ,
    oakcurric:thread-design ,
    oakcurric:thread-collage .

oakcurric:unit-2677
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "An overview of craft"@en ;
  curric:slug "an-overview-of-craft" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit explores the world of craft, learning practices and significance, and
  engaging in handmaking their own projects. Pupils will use specialist materials and tools,
  research notable craftspeople, and enhance their practical skills and appreciation for
  craftsmanship."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit introduces pupils to the rich tradition and contemporary
  practice of craft, broadening their understanding of art beyond conventional fine arts. It
  builds on their existing skills and encourages hands-on creativity, critical for their
  development as versatile artists. Understanding craft's role and techniques fosters respect
  for different art forms and cultivates a comprehensive skill set, preparing pupils for
  diverse artistic pursuits in secondary school and beyond.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2677-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2677-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2677-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2677-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2677-5 ;
  curric:id "2677"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.056621Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
